#---------------------------kubectl install ---------------
sudo curl -o kubectl https://amazon-eks.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/1.19.6/2021-01-05/bin/linux/amd64/kubectl
sudo chmod +x ./kubectl
sudo mv ./kubectl /usr/local/bin 
# -----------------------------eksctl install--------------------------------
sudo curl --silent --location "https://github.com/weaveworks/eksctl/releases/latest/download/eksctl_$(uname -s)_amd64.tar.gz" | tar xz -C /tmp
sudo mv /tmp/eksctl /usr/local/bin



Cluster & Node Management
kubectl cluster-info
Shows information about the Kubernetes cluster.

kubectl get nodes
Lists all nodes in the cluster.

kubectl describe node <node-name>
Provides detailed information about a specific node.

📦 Pod Management
kubectl get pods
Lists all pods in the current namespace.

kubectl get pods --all-namespaces
Lists pods across all namespaces.

kubectl describe pod <pod-name>
Shows detailed info about a specific pod.

kubectl logs <pod-name>
Displays logs from a pod.

kubectl exec -it <pod-name> -- /bin/bash
Accesses a running pod interactively.

📁 Deployment & ReplicaSet
kubectl get deployments
Lists all deployments.

kubectl describe deployment <deployment-name>
Shows detailed info about a deployment.

kubectl apply -f <file>.yaml
Creates or updates resources defined in a YAML file.

kubectl delete -f <file>.yaml
Deletes resources defined in a YAML file.

kubectl rollout status deployment/<deployment-name>
Checks the rollout status of a deployment.

kubectl scale deployment <deployment-name> --replicas=5
Scales the number of replicas.

🔄 Service Management
kubectl get services
Lists all services.

kubectl describe service <service-name>
Shows details of a specific service.

🧪 Namespace Management
kubectl get namespaces
Lists all namespaces.

kubectl create namespace <name>
Creates a new namespace.

kubectl config set-context --current --namespace=<name>
Sets the default namespace for the current context.

🧹 Cleanup & Debugging
kubectl delete pod <pod-name>
Deletes a pod.

kubectl delete deployment <deployment-name>
Deletes a deployment.

kubectl top pod
Shows resource usage of pods (requires metrics-server).
